                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Atkins is working very well for my wife and I.  She is down 15-20lbs (sh doesn't tell me exactly) and I am down 35lbs and 3 belt loops with 60lbs more to go for me.  We started it the Sunday after Thanksgiving.
<br />

<br />
Two things:  
<br />
1)  Atkins takes commitment from your entire household.  If your spuse/children aren't willing to support you and change their habits too then you will find it very difficult.
<br />
2)  Don't cheat.  There is no cheating on Atkins.  Say permanent bye bye to breads and sweets.  Get used to loving sugar free jello.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Atkins isn't a change in diet - it is a change of lifestyle and it works - period.
<br />

<br />
Atkins was easier for me than my wife because I am a meat/salt lover, whereas she was a sweets lover.  I still get to eat many of my favorite things.  My wife had a very difficult time in the first 2-3 weeks, but is much happier now that she is seeing results.
<br />

<br />
Justa thought for you.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="images/smiles/icon_pistoles.gif" alt="icon_pistoles.gif" border="0" />  Moderator of The Runes - <span style="font-weight: bold">AKA Griefer Police</span>!
