                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We have the books and are reading them.  People make mistakes with Atkins because they listen to others and don't read the books.  Just because something is low in carbs doesn't mean its good for you.  Just because something is high/med carbs doesn't mean it's bad for you.  Certain foods have benefits regardless of carb content.
<br />

<br />
Maximum reccomended time in the first stage of Atkins is 6 months, and then you are supposed to ease off, thus Atkins is not a long term solution, but you can temper yourself and realize how many carbs you used to eat.  Breads, potatos, sweets how much redeeming value does these actually have in your daily diet.  Minimizing them for the rest of your life can't be bad, but completely eliminating them for eternity shouldn't be an option either.  What Atkin's is mostly teaching my wife and I is awareness and discipline and these can help us for the rest of our lives.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="images/smiles/icon_pistoles.gif" alt="icon_pistoles.gif" border="0" />  Moderator of The Runes - <span style="font-weight: bold">AKA Griefer Police</span>!
