                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As far as diets and eatting healthy, I'm a firm believer of everything can kill you. For a while meat could kill you, then it was the pessticides on the vegetables that were bad, mad cow disease is back, carbohydrates are bad for you...seems like no matter what you eat, in a few months someone is going to come back and say oh we've proven that is bad for you.
<br />

<br />
Bascially what I do is try to stay at the "ideal" weight for my height. I don't eat properly, never really have, but take vitamins (just because my mom wouldn't stay off my case until I started taking them..and a mom nagging over the phone isn't a lot of fun) to supplement what I don't get outta food.
<br />

<br />
I also have to watch myself because my blood sugar likes to bottom out, I'm not diabetic or anything (yet at least) so I just have to be careful if I don't eat all day or something (course then I just go grab a candy bar or something)
<br />

<br />
But remember you have to be able to love yourself before you can expect anyone else to...and no matter how much you try, when you are unhappy with yourself it shows to others even when you don't think it does.
