                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm a guy here, but I figured I would give my 2 cents.  I am very familiar with hypo thyroidism as I have a pretty unique case.  I was born without a thyroid gland.  It's just not there.  Most doctors aside from specialists do not know much about the thyroid.  There are two ways your body can have thyroid problems. 
<br />

<br />
First your body can not produce enough thyroid.  This is the way most doctors interpret it.  They check how much is in your blood.
<br />

<br />
However, hypothyroidism can also be caused when your body is not efficient at using the thyroid it does have.  In this case your body needs "more" thyroid than what doctors would normally prescribe for you.  
<br />

<br />
It seemed to be a relatively new thing as doctors have just within the past 5 years told me about it, and I've been seeing doctors the past 22 years (since I was born.)
<br />

<br />
As for the Atkins diet, it can very well be lifetime.  In fact the lifetime maintenance program has been given good ratings by the New England Journal of Medicine.  Should you stay on the Induction Phase of less than 20 carbs a day your entire life?  No, but that's why people say to read the books.
<br />

<br />
As for the person who said Dr. Atkins died at a young age to heart failure, not sure where you read that but this is from the Atkins website.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">2003 Dr. Atkins dies of complications after severe head trauma sustained in an accident.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
By the way I believe he was 72 when he died, so not all that young either.
<br />

<br />
Anyways, just my two cents.  If anyone is interested in thyroid questions send me a server tell firiona.Zsuzsana.  God knows I've been a test for so many doctors might as well tell people who might benefit from the knowledge I have.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
