                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Dieting is great, but not really a solution all by itself.
<br />

<br />
The absolute best thing that you can do is exercise combined with sensible eating. The Body for Life web site can give you some good ideas about some simple eating plans and workout plans.
<br />

<br />
Even very simple things like taking the stairs at work instead of the elevator can do quite a bit. At the mall, walk up the stairs instead of taking the escalator. In the parking garage take the stairs instead of using the elevator.
<br />

<br />
If you can't walk up 5 flights of stairs (to the 5th floor of a building) without feeling tired, then you are probably not 'healthy' and you should combine sensible eating with light exercise.
<br />

<br />
The key to doing this is also pretty simple: Make it a habit. If you do the same thing every day (take a walk around the block, ride a bike, use the stairs at work) for 45 days... You have a new habit. Habits are VERY hard to break, but you can make GOOD habits just as you can make bad ones.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=166364" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Craftah</a> - Master of all languages and tradeskills.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
